&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="label"&gt;&lt;a class="fn-backref" href="#id1"&gt;[1]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;The principle of the constancy of the velocity of light is of course
contained in Maxwell’s equations.&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Albert Einstein</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 26 Sep 1905 00:15:00 -0517</pubDate><guid>tag:jpneira.net,1905-09-26:does-the-inertia-of-a-body-depend-on-its-energy-content.html</guid><category>paper</category><category>einstein</category><category>mass-energy equivalence</category></item></channel></rss>